==English==
===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French [[#French|essence]], from Latin [[essentia]], from an irregular formation of [[esse]] ‘be’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈɛsəns/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# the [[inherent]] [[nature]] of a thing or an idea
# a [[significant]] [[feature]] of something
# the [[concentrated]] form of a plant or drug obtained through a [[distillation]] process
#* ''essence of Jojoba''
# [[fragrance]], a [[perfume]]
# (''philosophy'') the true inward nature of anything, not accidental or [[illusory]]

====Translations====
{{checktrans}}
*Finnish: [[olemus]] (1), [[perusolemus]] (1), [[esanssi]] (4)

